Diagnosis. In both sexes: very wide head with coarse punctures; preoccipital ridge lamellate (
Fig. 24
); pronotal angle acute and projected; lateral areas of mesoscutum with punctures almost contiguous, becoming gradually sparsely punctured centrally, and surface between punctures micro-reticulate (
Fig. 24
). Male: S 4 with a central patch of hair as
C. psoraspis
(
Fig. 5
).
